All right.

02:00.288 --> 02:04.418
♪ Listening to the beat
of the streets of LA

02:06.127 --> 02:10.547
♪ Oh, every night, every
day I call you on the phone

02:10.548 --> 02:14.548
♪ Every night, every
day, I can't let you go

02:20.808 --> 02:21.428
Hey Dad.

02:21.434 --> 02:22.726
Did you see the news?

02:22.727 --> 02:23.437
Yeah, I'm looking at it now.

02:23.438 --> 02:27.226
They ordered the evacuation.

02:28.733 --> 02:29.613
Shut everything down.

02:29.614 --> 02:31.528
Put out the second
layer of sandbags,

02:31.529 --> 02:33.195
board up the rest
of the windows.

02:33.196 --> 02:34.446
Your mom's packing a few things,

02:34.447 --> 02:35.197
we'll stay with Uncle Marvin.

02:35.198 --> 02:38.617
Meet you here in half an hour?

02:38.618 --> 02:39.408
I'm prepping the fish Josh

02:39.410 --> 02:41.620
caught off Cape
May this weekend.

02:41.621 --> 02:43.121
- Well...
- It's gonna be a special.

02:43.122 --> 02:43.912
We're not going to be back
for at least a couple of days,

02:43.915 --> 02:47.417
so toss it.

02:47.418 --> 02:48.708
I'm gonna stay.

02:48.711 --> 02:49.878
What?

02:49.879 --> 02:51.169
Josh spent a half an hour
reelin' these things in.

02:51.172 --> 02:53.092
I've been here all
morning preppin'.

02:53.093 --> 02:54.591
I'll stay, watch over the place,

02:54.592 --> 02:55.801
to make sure nothing
happens, you know?

02:55.802 --> 02:57.260
It'll be fun.

02:57.261 --> 02:59.596
Look, kid, they're
closing the bridges down,

02:59.597 --> 03:01.217
if you don't come now...
He's not coming?

03:01.224 --> 03:03.272
They always say it's going
to be the worst one ever.

03:03.273 --> 03:05.185
Irene was supposed to be
the hundred year storm.

03:05.186 --> 03:05.976
That was last year, nothing
happened here at all.

03:05.978 --> 03:08.938
Your mother looks concerned.

03:08.940 --> 03:11.316
His mother is concerned.

03:11.317 --> 03:13.397
Please, don't
worry, either of you.

03:13.403 --> 03:16.033
I'll make sure nothing happens.

03:16.906 --> 03:17.776
Trust me.

03:18.741 --> 03:21.159
Alright.

03:21.160 --> 03:24.329
You call me if
anything happens, okay?

03:24.330 --> 03:28.540
Shame you're gonna
miss out on this sucker.

03:28.543 --> 03:29.393
Be safe.

03:41.514 --> 03:44.274
Come on, let's get in the car.

04:01.200 --> 04:05.410
♪ Ooh, I toss and
turn all night baby

04:08.583 --> 04:09.708
Dude.

04:09.709 --> 04:10.709
Ah, ha, ha.

04:11.878 --> 04:13.168
Holy shit.

04:13.171 --> 04:16.089
My recipe, not my dad's.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.219
His menu's been the
same since I was a kid.

04:18.220 --> 04:19.627
His cooking is driving me crazy.

04:19.635 --> 04:20.973
I want to make
food that surprises

04:20.974 --> 04:22.050
people like I did in New York.

04:22.053 --> 04:23.560
I don't care about the money.

04:23.561 --> 04:25.806
And now, you're back
here with the rest of us.

04:25.808 --> 04:29.978
♪ I'm on the edge
and about to fall

04:31.230 --> 04:33.565
Hurricane party 2012!

04:33.566 --> 04:36.436
Whoo!

04:39.155 --> 04:41.865
Hey, you're in college.

04:41.866 --> 04:43.486
You like doing shots?

04:43.493 --> 04:44.613
No.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.787
Come on.

04:46.788 --> 04:48.497
Water rising in the streets

04:48.498 --> 04:50.498
having breached many sea
walls and beach areas.

04:50.500 --> 04:53.170
Governor Christie in his
press conference saying...

04:53.171 --> 04:54.795
We're right next to the bay.

04:54.796 --> 04:56.296
Maybe we should put
out more sandbags.

04:56.297 --> 04:57.797
Nothing's gonna happen.

04:57.799 --> 05:01.129
Oh, so now you're
a climate scientist.

05:02.595 --> 05:03.305
Hell yes, damn right I am.

05:03.306 --> 05:05.764
I'm good at hurricane sports.

05:05.765 --> 05:07.474
As well as a food expert.

05:07.475 --> 05:08.985
Dude, I am whatever
the hell I wanna be.

05:08.986 --> 05:10.226
I got talent.

05:12.271 --> 05:13.361
Atlantic City High!
Whoo!

05:13.362 --> 05:15.606
At least you're
getting paid to cook.

05:15.608 --> 05:17.398
I do not get paid to cook food.

05:17.401 --> 05:20.070
I cook comfort food.
Dude, quit bitching.

05:20.071 --> 05:22.111
You quit bitching.

05:42.552 --> 05:43.002
Ah.

05:44.470 --> 05:46.346
- Oh, my God.
- Wow.

05:46.347 --> 05:47.637
It's everywhere.

05:54.814 --> 05:57.649
Dude, grab some more beers.

05:57.650 --> 05:59.400
Come on, ever dance
in a hurricane before?

05:59.402 --> 06:00.110
Let go!

06:00.111 --> 06:00.991
Go back inside.

06:00.992 --> 06:02.647
Terry, back inside!

06:02.655 --> 06:04.665
Ah, fuck that,
it's dark in there.

06:04.666 --> 06:06.657
Come on, this is amazing!

06:07.493 --> 06:09.828
And if it does
flood, I don't have

06:09.829 --> 06:12.869
to work in this
shit hole anymore.

06:12.874 --> 06:14.170
To not working in a shit hole.

06:14.171 --> 06:16.036
To not working in a shit hole!

06:16.043 --> 06:17.003
You guys are crazy!

06:17.004 --> 06:19.633
What if the water gets
in the restaurant?

06:19.634 --> 06:22.340
I don't care if
this place floods.

06:22.341 --> 06:24.050
I don't care if this
restaurant floods.

06:24.051 --> 06:24.931
Sam, oh, my god, stop.

06:24.932 --> 06:27.427
You know what?

06:27.430 --> 06:29.760
I don't care if this whole
piece of shit town floods!

06:29.765 --> 06:31.016
Sam!

06:31.017 --> 06:32.726
Oh shit.

06:32.727 --> 06:34.347
Ummm, dude, Sam.

06:34.353 --> 06:36.353
Sam, the water is getting in.

06:36.355 --> 06:38.023
- Oh, no.
- Oh, God.

06:38.024 --> 06:39.194
What are we gonna do?

06:39.195 --> 06:41.359
Shit, the sandbags.

06:41.360 --> 06:42.527
Come on, man, come on.

06:42.528 --> 06:43.568
Move the bags, we can stop it.

06:43.571 --> 06:44.361
Okay.

06:44.363 --> 06:45.241
Okay, I'm on it.

06:45.242 --> 06:46.029
Come on, come on, come on,

06:46.032 --> 06:46.782
Come on, pull it up.

06:46.783 --> 06:48.329
Come on, come on, pull it up.

06:48.330 --> 06:49.866
Pull the...
I'm trying!

06:49.869 --> 06:51.036
Come on!

06:51.037 --> 06:52.447
Agh!
Sam!

06:52.455 --> 06:53.793
Guys, it's at
my shoe, what do I do?

06:53.794 --> 06:54.707
It's on the
stairs, it's getting in.

06:54.708 --> 06:55.707
Shit!

06:55.708 --> 06:57.578
It's too late.

08:27.883 --> 08:31.473
Where have you been, we're
getting backed up in there.

08:31.474 --> 08:34.139
I just needed a minute.

08:34.140 --> 08:35.890
Another debt notice.

08:35.890 --> 08:37.390
A month past due.

08:45.484 --> 08:48.704
- Sam, how are ya?
- Alright.

08:49.321 --> 08:51.031
Good to see ya open.

08:51.032 --> 08:52.115
Thanks.

08:52.116 --> 08:54.156
Been a few months,
actually, tell your friends.

08:54.160 --> 08:55.910
I sure will.

08:55.911 --> 08:57.161
How high did the water get?

08:57.163 --> 08:58.163
Down in front it
was over the chairs.

08:58.164 --> 08:59.124
Water line up to here.

08:59.125 --> 09:00.961
Yeah, our place was flooded.

09:00.962 --> 09:03.748
We lost all kinds of stuff,
old photographs, clothes.

09:03.753 --> 09:04.173
We gotta re-do the
whole basement.

09:04.174 --> 09:06.629
Man.

09:06.630 --> 09:07.420
My cousin's place
in Ocean City's just gone.

09:07.423 --> 09:07.923
He's given up.

09:09.508 --> 09:11.008
Movin' in trying to...

09:11.010 --> 09:11.970
Well, he's been
there for twenty years.

09:11.971 --> 09:14.509
Yeah, at least, since college.

09:14.513 --> 09:16.313
Enjoy your meal, Terry.

09:16.314 --> 09:17.387
Thank you.

09:30.154 --> 09:32.739
♪ You've been busy

09:32.740 --> 09:35.700
♪ I've been healing time

09:35.701 --> 09:37.201
A little more vinegar.

09:37.203 --> 09:38.203
You got it.

09:38.204 --> 09:39.996
Hey!

09:39.997 --> 09:41.577
What is this?

09:41.582 --> 09:42.502
It's the salmon and white wine.

09:42.503 --> 09:44.250
No, I mean the fancy stuff.

09:44.251 --> 09:46.001
I told you.

09:47.630 --> 09:49.798
Simplify the presentation.

09:49.799 --> 09:50.879
I did.

09:50.883 --> 09:52.550
You are using an
extra ingredient that

09:52.551 --> 09:54.511
they're never gonna eat,
it's gonna take forever.

09:54.512 --> 09:55.262
Can't rush perfection.

09:55.263 --> 09:57.222
You gotta stop it, I mean it.

09:57.223 --> 09:59.723
You're not in New York anymore.

10:05.064 --> 10:07.565
We're out of clams again, man.

10:07.566 --> 10:09.436
Alright, I got it.

10:13.823 --> 10:14.613
Dude.

10:14.615 --> 10:15.495
Hey.

10:16.450 --> 10:19.080
We're paying you to
shuck cherry stones.

10:19.081 --> 10:24.118
I catch you on the phone again
you're gone, you hear me?

10:27.711 --> 10:29.131
Sorry about that.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.048
Do you have a light?

10:33.050 --> 10:33.930
Yeah.

10:48.274 --> 10:49.482
Thanks.

10:49.483 --> 10:52.110
Oh, thank you, no I don't smoke.

10:52.111 --> 10:55.280
In case the stove doesn't light.

10:55.281 --> 10:56.111
You a cook?

10:56.115 --> 10:57.782
Mmm-hmm.

10:57.783 --> 10:59.242
Well, the food is really
good, compliments to the chef.

10:59.243 --> 11:00.993
Thank you.

11:02.371 --> 11:04.956
Who is the chef,
is he well-known?

11:04.957 --> 11:06.827
Not really.

11:06.834 --> 11:08.084
It's me.

11:08.085 --> 11:08.965
Oh.

11:11.297 --> 11:13.547
There you are.

11:14.884 --> 11:16.594
You did, didn't you?

11:17.595 --> 11:19.429
Oh, no, that's,

11:19.430 --> 11:20.510
that's mine.

11:23.809 --> 11:25.349
This is the head chef.

11:25.352 --> 11:27.150
I was talking to him
about catering the party.

11:27.151 --> 11:27.766
Okay, right.

11:27.771 --> 11:28.811
So like I was saying,

11:28.814 --> 11:31.232
we're throwing a
party on Saturday.

11:31.233 --> 11:33.653
It's kind of last
minute, not much money.

11:33.654 --> 11:34.742
Like, 1,500?

11:35.988 --> 11:36.778
1,500?

11:36.780 --> 11:37.906
I know.

11:37.907 --> 11:40.237
It's short notice.

11:40.242 --> 11:41.332
I know some guys.

11:41.333 --> 11:42.487
Perfect.

11:42.494 --> 11:45.044
You're a lifesaver.

12:02.348 --> 12:04.348
- Ugh.
- You okay?

12:04.350 --> 12:05.640
Yeah.

12:05.643 --> 12:07.852
Can I get a whiskey
please, rocks?

12:07.853 --> 12:09.020
Sure.

12:09.021 --> 12:10.061
Any you'd prefer?

12:10.064 --> 12:11.524
Yeah, that one right there.

12:11.525 --> 12:12.773
That one's not for sale.

12:12.775 --> 12:15.485
It was a gift to
my dad from his dad

12:15.486 --> 12:16.945
when he took over the place.

12:16.946 --> 12:20.986
Alright, I'll have,
uh, one of those.

12:22.117 --> 12:22.987
Yeah.

12:27.414 --> 12:29.666
Is he coming over here?

12:29.667 --> 12:30.457
Yep.

12:30.459 --> 12:30.959
Shit.

12:30.960 --> 12:31.420
Mister Blake.

12:31.421 --> 12:33.586
Hi.

12:33.587 --> 12:35.207
Roger Bell, Leopold Bank.

12:35.214 --> 12:36.174
How are you sir?

12:36.175 --> 12:37.340
Good to see you, Roger.

12:37.341 --> 12:38.381
Good to see you, too,
and I wanted to thank

12:38.384 --> 12:40.052
you for reaching out with
the redevelopment deal.

12:40.053 --> 12:41.392
You asked for me
personally, huh?

12:41.393 --> 12:42.845
I heard good things.

12:42.846 --> 12:45.006
Okay, well I guess those,
uh, bribes are payin' off.

12:45.976 --> 12:48.231
But we could uh, we
could talk business

12:48.232 --> 12:49.936
on Saturday at the
party, you're coming?

12:49.937 --> 12:51.437
Charlie put it
in all my gadgets.

12:51.438 --> 12:52.728
- Roger?
- Yeah?

12:52.731 --> 12:54.021
They're pulling the car around.

12:54.024 --> 12:54.774
Oh, Mister Blake, have
you met my wife, Sarah?

12:54.775 --> 12:55.733
No, I haven't.

12:55.734 --> 12:56.694
It's a pleasure.

12:56.695 --> 12:58.069
The food here is amazing.

12:58.070 --> 12:58.860
Yes, it is.

12:58.862 --> 12:59.612
I hope you enjoy it.

12:59.613 --> 13:00.243
I've been here before.

13:00.244 --> 13:02.279
It's great, thank you.

13:03.784 --> 13:06.914
Okay, we'll see you at the
party, have a nice night.

13:09.248 --> 13:10.618
Hit me again.

13:24.346 --> 13:25.216
Hey!

13:25.222 --> 13:26.102
You okay?

13:27.641 --> 13:28.221
Hello there.

13:30.102 --> 13:31.770
I think you
could use a ride home.

13:31.771 --> 13:32.560
No.

13:32.563 --> 13:33.273
No, no.

13:33.274 --> 13:35.112
I'm an excellent drunk driver.

13:39.570 --> 13:40.070
Hey.
Come on.

13:42.239 --> 13:43.489
Let's go.

13:43.490 --> 13:45.408
Switch with me.

13:45.409 --> 13:46.576
Alright.

13:46.577 --> 13:48.157
I mean,
on the news, the governors

13:48.162 --> 13:49.702
in Washington saying
they got all this money,

13:49.705 --> 13:51.914
I put in my claim five months
ago, I still got nothing.

13:51.915 --> 13:54.754
I mean I'm staying in
Glasboro with my sister.

13:54.755 --> 13:57.252
The house is a wreck, the first
floor has mud on the floor,

13:57.254 --> 13:58.796
and it has to be gutted.

13:58.797 --> 14:00.627
The whole thing is just,
it just gets to a point

14:00.632 --> 14:04.385
where you just wonder,
is it time to give it up?

14:04.386 --> 14:05.886
Go find work somewhere else.

14:05.888 --> 14:07.758
God, I lived there
my whole life.

14:15.439 --> 14:17.899
Um, hi, Ma'am.

14:18.317 --> 14:19.277
Uh, your husband...

14:19.278 --> 14:20.436
He's not my husband.

14:20.444 --> 14:21.991
I'm not, she's not my,

14:21.992 --> 14:23.527
I'm not her husband.
Oh.

14:23.530 --> 14:24.240
I run his company.

14:24.241 --> 14:28.329
Honey, I'm home.

14:30.162 --> 14:31.202
Is he drunk?

14:34.875 --> 14:38.753
Of all the things
I own, this spot,

14:38.754 --> 14:41.506
the best thing I
ever spent money on.

14:41.507 --> 14:42.877
It's a hell of a view.

14:42.883 --> 14:47.220
Yeah, it took a beating during
the storm, but we rebuilt.

14:47.221 --> 14:48.101
Here you go.

14:48.102 --> 14:49.507
Oh, um, thanks.

14:50.015 --> 14:52.350
Coffee? Come on.

14:52.351 --> 14:54.351
Thank you for driving him.

14:54.353 --> 14:55.353
Yeah.

15:00.359 --> 15:01.189
Ah.

15:02.694 --> 15:06.280
You should really try that.

15:06.281 --> 15:08.371
It's Belvenie, thirty years old.

15:08.372 --> 15:10.117
It's a limited edition.

15:15.040 --> 15:15.830
Oh.

15:15.833 --> 15:16.583
Oh?

15:16.584 --> 15:18.167
Yeah.

15:18.168 --> 15:20.708
This is amazing, right?
It's good.

15:20.712 --> 15:22.132
I am so hungry.

15:23.215 --> 15:24.423
Yeah?

15:24.424 --> 15:25.934
Are you hungry?

15:26.927 --> 15:28.177
So, one of my mentors
in culinary school

15:28.178 --> 15:32.056
told me cuisine is the
mark of a healthy society.

15:32.057 --> 15:34.177
Barbarians, Vikings, aren't
known for their food.

15:34.184 --> 15:36.563
If you're focused on survival,
you only have time for,

15:36.564 --> 15:37.602
for what's good enough.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.898
But cuisine isn't about
what's good enough.

15:40.899 --> 15:43.317
It's about how good can it be.

15:43.318 --> 15:44.735
You went to culinary school?

15:44.736 --> 15:45.696
New York.

15:45.697 --> 15:47.486
Oh, mmm, thank you.

15:50.200 --> 15:51.740
Oh, my god.

15:51.743 --> 15:52.833
I have had eggs like
a million times.

15:52.834 --> 15:55.408
They've never been so soft.

15:56.665 --> 15:57.335
You outta open your own place.

15:57.336 --> 15:59.167
I did.

15:59.168 --> 16:00.418
You did, what happened?

16:00.419 --> 16:01.377
I'm workin' in my Dad's kitchen,

16:01.378 --> 16:02.298
what do you think happened?

16:02.299 --> 16:03.746
Well, you've got talent.

16:03.755 --> 16:05.343
In my experience, talent
and hard work rarely pay off.

16:05.344 --> 16:06.380
Connections, capital
and willingness

16:06.383 --> 16:09.427
to appeal to the lowest
common denominator?

16:09.428 --> 16:10.298
Cha-ching.

16:12.431 --> 16:14.771
Uh, thank you for the drink,

16:16.226 --> 16:17.886
but I should probably go, I
got some friends waiting on me.

16:17.895 --> 16:19.228
Now, where you headed?

16:19.229 --> 16:20.189
The Clove.

16:20.189 --> 16:21.149
Can I come?

16:26.904 --> 16:28.154
Hey!

16:28.155 --> 16:29.363
This is my friend, Mister Blake.

16:29.364 --> 16:30.162
Hi, Tom.

16:30.163 --> 16:30.907
Tom.

16:30.908 --> 16:32.278
Nice to meet you.

16:33.285 --> 16:34.455
How's it goin'?

16:35.037 --> 16:37.157
Next round is on me.

16:43.253 --> 16:47.632
♪ You know you got me
goin' out of my mind

16:47.633 --> 16:50.053
♪ And I would take a
bullet for these fancy lies

16:50.054 --> 16:54.262
♪ You know you got me
goin' out of my mind

16:55.641 --> 16:56.471
Six shots.

16:56.475 --> 16:58.226
Yeah.

16:58.227 --> 16:59.017
I need money.

16:59.019 --> 17:00.309
How much?

17:00.312 --> 17:00.982
Uh, like, like, 30?

17:00.983 --> 17:03.309
No, no, no, hey, hey, hey!

17:03.315 --> 17:03.815
Hey, hey, hey!

17:03.816 --> 17:05.358
I got it!

17:16.411 --> 17:16.901
Alright.

17:38.350 --> 17:39.180
What, what, hey!

17:39.184 --> 17:40.643
What the hell are you doin'?

17:40.644 --> 17:41.234
Just zippin' up.

17:41.235 --> 17:42.687
Just get in the car.

17:42.688 --> 17:44.358
Get in, get in, get in, get in!

17:44.359 --> 17:46.226
Hey, come back here.

17:46.233 --> 17:47.400
Bye.

17:50.112 --> 17:52.862
This is a crazy fucking city!

17:52.864 --> 17:53.994
Yeah! Whoo!

17:56.285 --> 17:57.205
I haven't done
that in a long time.

17:57.206 --> 17:59.452
Make out with a
girl half your age?

